      • connect

        public Response connect(String connectionName,
                        String ipAndPort,
                        String user,
                        String password)
        Description copied from interface: SftpExecutor
        Creates an SFTP session and caches the session mapped to a connectionName string. For Solace appliances, FTP-Users have different credentials than CLI users, so please note that sessions authenticated with CLI credentials will NOT succeed at executing SFTP operations.
        Specified by:
        connect in interface SftpExecutor
        Parameters:
        connectionName - Name (NOT a wildcard expression) assigned to this session for retrieval in disconnect, execute, and executeScript commands.
        ipAndPort - The IP:port to connect to. If no port is provided, port 22 is assumed.
        user - Username to authenticate with.
        password - Password to authenticate with username.
        Returns:
        The connection status and initial text output from the session upon connection.
        See Also:
        Response
